["The store is top-notch! I visited the store because of its fame with huge beef and numerous noodle.

Around the store there are neither nearby YouBike decks nor train stations. The nearest MRT station is approximately 10 mins on foot away from the store.

At first when I came to the store, it was fully packed with many customers, so I could hardly access the store. I ordered a small bowl of beef noodle, and they fetched me a SUPER big bowl. I initially thought that they probably incorrectly gave me that. However, after ascertaining that with the waiter, it turned out that the size I ordered is truly the smaller one.

The size for their small bowl is as huge as normal big size bowl from most restaurants or eateries in Taiwan. Therefore, my suggestion is that for those have big appetite, you won’t be regret to have a giant bowl from their store.

After having the meal, it’s also good to stroll a little for digestion until arrive at the MRT Zishan Station.

Zhongcheng's beef noodle is how I remember Taiwanese Beef noodle tastes. Will most definitely stop in the next time I am in Taipei.","In the lively lanes of Taipei, you'll find a place that has been consistently serving up something special - a comforting, homestyle bowl of beef noodle soup. This place is none other than Zhongcheng Beef Noodle Restaurant, a local favorite that has quietly withstood the test of time.

What makes Zhongcheng so beloved is its broth, a carefully crafted blend of dark soy, tomato, and red chili. This is not just any broth - it's the result of a family recipe, passed down through generations, its secrets zealously guarded.

The stewards of this tradition are a pair of sisters who have been running the place for over 20 years. They've made it their mission to provide good value to their customers, a promise they uphold with bowls that are generously filled, bucking the trend of smaller portions around the city.

Their noodles are thick and chewy, perfect for soaking up the flavorful broth. As for the beef, it comes in two forms: shanks and tendons. The tendons are juicy, with a pleasant gelatinous texture, while the shanks are tender and packed with flavor.

The beef noodle soup is often served with a side of tea eggs and seaweed, simple but classic accompaniments that round out the meal. And to complete the experience, you're encouraged to wash it all down with a crisp Apple Sidra soda.

Zhongcheng Beef Noodle Restaurant is a gem in Taipei's dining scene, a tribute to the enduring appeal of a well-loved dish. It's a place I always make a point of visiting whenever I'm in town. It's not flashy, it's not fancy, but it's undeniably satisfying, and sometimes, that's all you really need","Service","Service","Dine in","Dine in","","Meal type","Meal type","Lunch","Lunch","","Price per person","Price per person","$1–200","$1–200","","Nice taste, it's my old memory about beef noodle flavor, big chunk beef, strong soup flavor, and 外省 taste. AiReviewSummary: This restaurant, Zhongcheng Beef Noodle Restaurant, is famous for its huge beef portions and delicious noodle soup. I visited the store and was surprised by the large serving, which is actually a smaller option. The noodle soup is very flavorful, and the beef is tender and amazing. The place is perfect for those with big appetites, and it's a good value for the price. The soup is a bit too heavy, but it's delicious and value for money. It's recommended to stroll a little after eating to help with digestion. They serve a variety of dishes, including beef noodle, beef noodle soup, tea eggs, and seaweed, which are all good.

Upon arrival, guests are warmly welcomed at the reception desk on the first floor of Taipei 101 and promptly escorted to their reserved table by the attentive wait staff.

Arriving at 2:45pm during lunch hour, our brief wait for the wait staff to escort us to our reserved table lasted approximately 5-10 minutes, ensuring a smooth entry process. The restaurant's unique circular seating arrangement, positioned near the expansive glass windows, affords diners uninterrupted views of Taipei's skyline. Additionally, the circular layout of the food stations simplifies navigation, allowing guests to explore the diverse culinary offerings effortlessly.

The buffet presents an impressive array of dishes, showcasing a fusion of international cuisines to cater to diverse dietary preferences. Standout highlights include the tantalizing fire-grilled sushi, succulent freshly grilled steaks and pork ribs, and an assortment of meticulously crafted artisanal coffee and cocktails. Noteworthy is the chef's personalized attention at the steak and pork rib station, where each dish is expertly plated in French style, elevating the dining experience.

Reflecting on the meal, while the price-performance ratio may not be the highest due to the absence of standout premium ingredients, the buffet's emphasis on luxury dining justifies its price point. It remains a worthwhile culinary journey, particularly for discerning travelers seeking an indulgent experience in Taiwan. Priced at over 4,000 NTD per person, the restaurant's commitment to menu uniqueness and ingredient quality shines through.

A thoughtful touch is the provision of postcards at each table, allowing guests to pen their sentiments on the spot and deposit them in a special mailbox. We were pleasantly surprised to receive our postcard a month later at our address in Madrid, Spain, a testament to the restaurant's dedication to guest satisfaction and attention to detail. Overall, the buffet at Taipei 101 offers an unforgettable dining experience that seamlessly blends luxury, gastronomy, and breathtaking views.","Service","Service","Dine in","Dine in","","Meal type","Meal type","Lunch","Lunch","","Price per person","Price per person","$2,000+","$2,000+","","Food: 4","Food: 4","","Service: 5","Service: 5","","Atmosphere: 5","Atmosphere: 5","","Recommended dishes","Recommended dishes","聯名甜點, 101雞蛋糕","聯名甜點, 101雞蛋糕","","","Had dinner last night. The food and the view of Taipei 101 were undoubtedly the highlights of the day, justifying the high price of 3680 TWD per person. The dishes were creatively crafted, combining fresh ingredients with innovative culinary techniques, and the stunning view of the city skyline added a special charm to the meal.

However, the service and facilities fell short of expectations. Firstly, while I was in the restroom, my friend was rushed to pay the bill twice within a span of less than 10 minutes, despite having informed the staff that I would be handling the payment. This created an uncomfortable and rushed dining experience, which was not in line with the standard expected at such a premium establishment.

Secondly, the restroom facilities were inadequate. With only three stalls available in the men's restroom, I had to wait for an extended period of time. Surprisingly, one of the stalls was occupied by a staff member, raising concerns about staff using the same facilities during work hours, especially when customer demand is high. For a high-end buffet charging over 3000 TWD, the restroom facilities were not only insufficient but also paled in comparison to much less expensive establishments.

In summary, while A Joy excels in culinary expertise and offers a mesmerizing view, the service approach and restroom facilities significantly dampened the overall experience. AiReviewSummary: The buffet at Taipei 101 is amazing! It's high above the city with a great view. The food is high class and there are tons of options to choose from. You can find dishes like lobsters, oysters, and abalones, which are really good. Although it's quite expensive, it's a great experience. The service is awesome and the staff are very polite.
